Poppy Smart complained to police after she was wolf-whistled at by builders on her way to work in Worcester city centre . 
  Marketing co-ordinator said she was harassed for a month by men on the building site . 
  She recorded the whistles on her phone and complained to the police and one of the builders . 
  Ms Smart also contacted the building company to complain of sexual harassment . 
  The 23-year-old said the whistling made her walk to work an 'awful experience'